description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a well-motivated Higher Clerical Officer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rewarding yet challenging role is set in the Department of Sexual Health (DoSH) at the Cardiff Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of a team you will be the first point of contact for patients and be liaising closely with senior staff members to ensure the smooth running of the clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to be involved in this dynamic and supportive service, have excellent communication and organisational skills, we look forward to your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 30 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and informal visits please contact Lydia Harrison, Administration and Operational Manager on lydia.harrison@wales.nhs.uk or 07811423819&lt;/p&gt;
